Sure! To write an if/then statement in C programming language, you can use the following syntax:

if (condition) {
  // Code to be executed if the condition is true
} else {
  // Code to be executed if the condition is false
}

Here are some examples of if/then statements in C:

if (x > 5) {
  printf("x is greater than 5\n");
} else {
  printf("x is not greater than 5\n");
}

If you want to nest if/then statements, you can use the else if statement like this:

if (x > 5) {
  printf("x is greater than 5\n");
} else if (x < 5) {
  printf("x is less than 5\n");
} else {
  printf("x is equal to 5\n");
}

For more information on writing if/then statements in C, you can check out the C programming language reference at https://www.tutorialspoint.com/cprogramming/c_if_else.htm.
